I find jazz music problematic.
I have no-- Nothing against jazz musicians.
I'm sure people enjoy it, but the problem with jazz is that my mind--
I immediately think, "This is jazz,"
as opposed to really enjoying the song.
That's the problem I have, is it just-- Right away, I'm like, "Oh, this is jazz."
My belief is that everyone here has the same problem.
And to prove it, I'm gonna play some-- some real jazz.

when you feel like, "Oh, I'm sort of checking out a little bit, "

there must have been a time where doo-wop music
was the hardest music you've ever heard. Right? It only makes sense.
There was a time where someone heard doo-wop and was like,
"This is too much. This is too loud. Turn it down."
So, I'm gonna do my impression of a guy in the '50s,
